{{ 'dspln-artwork-page.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

<section class="dspln-artwork dspln-artwork-hero" aria-label="Artwork guidelines">
  <div class="dspln-artwork-hero__inner">
    <div class="dspln-artwork-hero__copy">
      <p class="dspln-artwork-eyebrow">ARTWORK GUIDELINES</p>
      <p class="dspln-artwork-hero__intro">
        Have questions about our artwork, files or embroidery? Find quick answers here. Need detailed instructions and specs? Scroll down.
      </p>

      <div class="dspln-artwork-faq">
        <details>
          <summary>What is the best file format?</summary>
          <p>PNG files are preferred due to their superior quality. Ensure they have a transparent background. Keep their size under 4MB and dimensions at least 4 inches wide.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>What size will my logos be?</summary>
          <p>All logos will be embroidered at a width of 4 inches, specifically on the left chest, sleeves, and pants. On the back of the kimono, they will be embroidered at a width of 10 inches. If you prefer smaller measurements, or a very specific placement of your logos, please leave a note for us during checkout.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>How can I remove the background?</summary>
          <p>You can find excellent websites where you can upload your logo and have the background removed automatically for free. One such website is <a href="https://www.remove.bg/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.remove.bg</a>.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>How can I get some logos made?</summary>
          <p>There are fantastic websites available that don't require any prior design or software knowledge. The most popular one is Canva. Additionally, there are amazing AI-powered platforms where you can generate artwork effortlessly. If you're interested in a customized design service, feel free to contact us, and I can provide you with pricing details.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="dspln-artwork-hero__media">
      <img
        src="{{ 'dspln-artwork-fighter.webp' | asset_url }}"
        alt=""
        width="1600"
        height="1600"
        loading="lazy"
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "DSPLN artwork FAQ",
  "settings": [],
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "DSPLN artwork FAQ"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
